body:
I have a testbench that calls a lot of tasks with timing controls in a initial block. Verilator generates a 9MB+ cpp file. It takes forever to compile. Here is a testcase that also generate a large cpp file (2.7MB).
[t_coroutine_split.tar.gz](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/files/11760393/t_coroutine_split.tar.gz)

In V3Sched [`orderSequentially`](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/blob/d1ff81a41c75ae4568bcb6d4f8f0cbc5688e76a1/src/V3Sched.cpp#L214), a suspendable procedure will be convert to a separate function and be replaced with a function call statement. But [`splitCheck`](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/blob/d1ff81a41c75ae4568bcb6d4f8f0cbc5688e76a1/src/V3Sched.cpp#L122) is never used to check that new function.

I've tried simply adding `splitCheck` in orderSequentially:
```diff
@@ -254,8 +254,11 @@ void orderSequentially(AstCFunc* funcp, const LogicByScope& lbs) {
                             bodyp
                                 = new AstWhile{flp, new AstConst{flp, AstConst::BitTrue{}}, bodyp};
                         }
+                        subFuncp->addStmtsp(bodyp);
+                        splitCheck(subFuncp);
+                    } else {
+                      subFuncp->addStmtsp(bodyp);
                     }
-                    subFuncp->addStmtsp(bodyp);
                 }
             } else {
                 logicp->unlinkFrBack();
```

Verilated code splits into smaller files, but there are errors during compilation.

``` log
Vt_coroutine_split___024root__DepSet_h18267415__0.cpp: In function ‘VlCoroutine Vt_coroutine_split___024root___eval_initial__TOP__0(Vt_coroutine_split___024root*)’:
Vt_coroutine_split___024root__DepSet_h18267415__0.cpp:41:1: warning: no return statement in function returning non-void [-Wreturn-type]
   41 | }
      | ^
Vt_coroutine_split___024root__DepSet_h18267415__0.cpp: In function ‘void Vt_coroutine_split___024root___eval_initial__TOP__0__0(Vt_coroutine_split___024root*)’:
Vt_coroutine_split___024root__DepSet_h18267415__0.cpp:48:5: error: unable to find the promise type for this coroutine
   48 |     co_await vlSelf->__VtrigSched_h7a97c1b5__0.trigger(0U,
      |     ^~~~~~~~
```
Any ideas?
